<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[2027,2614,633,1059]" pageId="21" pageNumber="147">
Recent microsatellite data and mtDNA show a monophyletic lineage, suggest ing that present species has maintained a large panmictic population since diverging from the 
<taxonomicName box="[2214,2353,912,941]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" genus="Leopardus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="21" pageNumber="147" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pardalis">L. pardalis</taxonomicName>
line. Phylogenetic analyses failed to confirm the four currently recognized subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
